    <!-- FAQ Section -->
    <section class="landing-section">
      <div class="landing-section-inner">
        <p class="section-label">Common Questions</p>
        <h2 class="section-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
        <div class="faq-list">
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">What do I need to run Soleur?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">For the self-hosted version, you need the Claude Code CLI with an Anthropic API key or a Claude subscription. Alternatively, you can run Soleur using Ollama via the <code>ollama launch</code> command. First, add the Soleur marketplace with <code>claude plugin marketplace add jikig-ai/soleur</code>, then install with <code>claude plugin install soleur</code> and run <code>/soleur:go</code> to start. No additional dependencies or server setup needed. The cloud platform (coming soon) requires only a browser and a Soleur subscription.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Does Soleur work on Windows, Linux, and macOS?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">The self-hosted version runs anywhere Claude Code runs &mdash; Linux, macOS, and Windows via WSL. The cloud platform will be accessible from any browser on any operating system.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">How much does Soleur cost?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">The self-hosted version is free and open source. Your costs depend entirely on your Claude usage through Anthropic. The cloud platform will offer paid tiers starting at $49/month for managed infrastructure, priority support, and team features.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">What is the difference between /soleur:go and individual skills?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer"><code>/soleur:go</code> is the unified entry point that classifies your intent and routes to the right workflow automatically. Individual skills like brainstorm, plan, work, and review can be invoked directly when you know exactly which stage you need.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">Can I use Soleur with an existing project?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">Yes. Run <code>/soleur:sync</code> to analyze your codebase and populate the knowledge base with your project&rsquo;s conventions, architecture, and patterns. Soleur adapts to your existing codebase rather than requiring a fresh start.</p>
          </details>
          <details class="faq-item">
            <summary class="faq-question">What is the difference between the cloud platform and self-hosted?</summary>
            <p class="faq-answer">The self-hosted version gives you the full platform &mdash; every agent, every skill, every department &mdash; running locally through the Claude Code CLI. The cloud platform adds a web dashboard, managed infrastructure, real-time agent orchestration, team collaboration, and priority support. Both versions access the same {{ stats.agents }} agents and {{ stats.skills }} skills.</p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
